{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> παρά-στᾰσις</b>, εως, ἡ, <br /> <br /><Level2><b>__I</b></Level2> (παρίστημι) <b>putting aside, removal</b>, especially <b>relegation, banishment</b>, π. ἐπὶ τὰ τῆς χώρας ἔσχατα [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Leges” 855c \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ἀποδημητικὰς ποιεῖσθαι τὰς π. αὐτῶν, i.e. to ostracize them, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Politica” 1308b19 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; παράστασις· φυγή, καὶ τὸ φυγαδεῦσαι παραστήσασθαι, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.AD(?): Hesychius Legal icographus \">Refs 5th c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__I.2</b></Level3> <b>display, exposure for sale</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Politica” 1258b23. \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__I.3</b></Level3> generally, <b>setting forth, exhibition, manifestation</b>, εἰς τύπωσιν καὶ π. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st c.BC: Philodemus Gadarensis Epigrammaticus “Rh.” 2.34 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; πρὸς παράστασίν τινος <b>placing before one, representation</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Arrianus Historicus “Epicteti Dissertationes” 2.19.1, 1st c.AD: Cornutus Philosophus “de Natura Deorum” 12, 2nd c.AD: Soranus Medicus “Vit.Hp.” 12, compare 3rd c.AD: Porphyrius Tyrius Philosophus “de Antro Nympharum - Porphyrii Opuscula” 4, 5th c.AD: Proclus Philosophus “in Prm.” p 504 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus, 5th-6th c.AD: Damascius Philosophus “de Principiis” 46, 301; κατὰ ἀπόφασιν ὧν οὐκ ἔστιν, οὐ κατὰ παράστασιν ὧν ἐστι προσηγόρευται 3rd c.AD: Porphyrius Tyrius Philosophus “Sententiae ad intelligibilia ducentes” 19. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level4><b>__I.3.b</b></Level4> εἰς π. τινός in <b>proof</b> of, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Galenus Medicus 1.149. \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__I.4</b></Level3> <b>placing beside</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd-3rd c.AD: Dio Cassius Historicus 42.48. \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__I.5</b></Level3> <b>production</b> in court, etc., π. προσώπων [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “POxy.” 1033.17 (4th c.AD). \">Refs 4th c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__I.6</b></Level3> ἡ π. τῶν δημοσίων the <b>provision</b> of public sacrificial victims, i. e. the revenues earmarked for that purpose, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “SIG” 562.68 (Paros, 3rd c.BC). \">Refs 3rd c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> (παρίσταμαι) <i>intransitive</i>, <b>being beside</b>: <br /><Level3><b>__II.1</b></Level3> <b>position</b> or <b>post near</b> a king, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Institutio Cyri (Cyropaedia)” 8.4.5. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.2</b></Level3> <b>arrival, visit</b>, στρατηγοῦ [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “POxy.” 2139 (2nd-3rd c.AD). \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.3</b></Level3> <b>assistance, succour</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “JHS” 37.101 (Lydia, 2nd c.AD) \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]; <b>manifestation</b> of divinity, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “SIG” 695.12 (5th c.BC: Magnes Comicus Mae., 2nd c.BC) \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; αἱ τῶν εἰδώλων π. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “Placita Philosophorum” 5.2.1. \">Refs</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.4</b></Level3> <b>proximity, presence</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.AD: Damascius Philosophus “de Principiis” 145, 394 \">Refs 5th c.AD+</a>]; ἀνάγκης π. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st c.BC: Philodemus Philosophus “Academicorum Index” p.54 M. \">Refs 1st c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.5</b></Level3> <b>room, space</b> for standing, οὐχ ἕξει π. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 3rd-2nd c.BC: Philo Mechanicus “(Belopoeica) Excerpte aus Philons Mechanik - Ath. Berl. Akad.” 85.3, compare 1st c.BC: Diodorus Siculus Historicus 20.91 \">Refs 3rd c.BC+</a>]: in <i>plural</i>, <b>free spaces</b> adjoining a line of wall, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “SIG” 1182.5,10(= 936 note, Ephesus, 3rd c.BC). \">Refs 3rd c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.6</b></Level3> <b>pomp, magnificence</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" LXX.1Mac.15.32. \">LXX</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.7</b></Level3> <b>mental excitement, ardour, exaltation</b>, μεγίστη π. εἶχέ τινας, ὡς δικαίως πράττοντας [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.BC: Polybius Historicus 5.9.6; μετὰ παραστάσεως ἠσπάζετο [prev. author] 10.5.4. \">Refs 2nd c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level4><b>__II.7.b</b></Level4> <b>desperate courage</b>, ὁρμὴ καὶ π. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] 3.63.14; μετὰ παραστάσεως ἠγωνίζοντο [prev. author] 16.33.2; ἡ ἐν ταῖς βασάνοις π. τῆς ψυχῆς 1st c.BC: Diodorus Siculus Historicus 10.17, compare 1st c.AD: Josephus Historicus “Bellum Judaicum” 2.20.7. \">Refs 1st c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level4><b>__II.7.c</b></Level4> <b>fury, desperation</b>, τὸ λυποῦν ἤγαγ᾽ ἐς π. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Antiphanes Comicus 104, compare 2nd c.BC: Polybius Historicus 8.21.4, 9.40.4; ἡ π. τῆς διανοίας [prev. author] 3.84.9. \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level4><b>__II.7.d</b></Level4> <b>propensity, desire</b>, ψυχῆς πονηρᾶς δυσσεβὴς π. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-3rd c.BC: Menander Comicus 540.8 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; ἄλογος π. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-3rd c.BC: Epicurus Philosophus “Epistulae” 1p.30U.; π. πρός τινα [prev. author] “fragment” 138; π. ψυχῆς πρὸς ἐλευθερίαν 1st c.BC: Diodorus Siculus Historicus 33.16 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; <b>impulse</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus 2.589a \">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>]; ἡ π. τῆς ψυχῆς, as gloss on{λῆμα}, Ps.-[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Herodianus Grammaticus Gr. post Moer. p.470 P. \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__III</b></Level2> as law-term, <b>money deposit, court fee</b> on entering certain public suits, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Andocides Orator 1.120, 4th c.BC: Isaeus Orator 3.47, 4th c.BC: Demetrius Phalereus Historicus “fragment” 7 1st c.AD: Josephus Historicus; π., μία δραχμή 4th-3rd c.BC: Menander Comicus 327, compare “Comica Adespota” 778, 1st-2nd c.AD: Harpocratio Grammaticus (which see) \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]","strongNumber":"G8638","accentedUnicode":"παράστασις","shortDef":"position","mediumDef":"position","stepGloss":"position","stepTransliteration":"parastasis","count":0,"_step_Type":"word"}]}